Discord Connection Issues

-Override on_disconnect and on_resumed to log when the bot drops and reconnects
-When the bot resumes, re-snapshot all watched channels and reconcile against what was recorded before the drop — members who left/joined during the outage would otherwise be missed
-Track a "disconnected at" timestamp so you know how big the gap was and can flag reports that had an outage during them

503 / API Errors (already in your TODOs)

-Wrap channel.send() calls in a retry loop with exponential backoff
-Do the same for any channel.members lookups during job startup

Job / Task Failures

-Wrap job_start internals in a broader try/except so unexpected exceptions don't silently kill a task — at minimum log them and notify the report channel
-If a task dies unexpectedly, attempt to auto-restart it if there's still time left in the watch window

Data Safety

-Periodically flush attendance data to a local file (your log file TODO) so if the bot crashes mid-job, you don't lose everything
-On startup, check for any leftover recovery files and alert an admin that a crash occurred

Reporting

-Flag the final attendance report if a disconnect was detected during that job's watch window, so the person reading it knows the data may have gaps
-Include the total outage duration in the report if one occurred

General Hygiene

-Add a global on_error handler to catch anything that slips through
-Add startup validation — confirm all channels in a job still exist and the bot still has permission to see them before the job begins watching
